      <h3 style="margin:0 0 10px">Example: How We Move Your Data to Your New Zorin Computer</h3>

      <h4 style="margin:14px 0 6px">Step 1 – Collecting Your Files</h4>
      <p>We begin by connecting a USB flash drive or external hard drive to your old PC or Mac. This becomes the “moving truck” for your digital belongings.</p>

      <h4 style="margin:14px 0 6px">Step 2 – Packing Up</h4>
      <p>We carefully copy your important folders—Documents, Pictures, Music, Desktop, and anything else you choose—onto the USB drive. If your old computer has multiple user profiles, we’ll gather the files from each one so no one’s data is left behind.</p>

      <h4 style="margin:14px 0 6px">Step 3 – Safe Transfer</h4>
      <p>Once everything is copied, we safely remove the USB and connect it to your new Zorin OS computer.</p>

      <h4 style="margin:14px 0 6px">Step 4 – Unpacking on Zorin OS</h4>
      <p>We place your files into the right spots on Zorin—Documents, Pictures, Music—so everything is organized and familiar. If there were multiple profiles on your old computer, we’ll create matching profiles on Zorin and place each person’s files in their own account.</p>

      <h4 style="margin:14px 0 6px">Step 5 – Secure Login Setup</h4>
      <p>When you receive your new Zorin PC or Mac, we provide a temporary password for each user profile. Along with it, you’ll get simple step-by-step instructions on how to change the password to something unique and personal to you.</p>

      <h4 style="margin:16px 0 8px">✅ What this means for you:</h4>
      <ul style="margin:0 0 12px 20px">
        <li>We handle the entire transfer process from start to finish.</li>
        <li>All personal files, from all profiles, move safely from the old computer to your new Zorin system.</li>
        <li>Everyone gets their own account on Zorin, just like before.</li>
        <li>You start with a secure temporary password, and then set your own personal password.</li>
        <li>No cloud accounts, complicated tools, or tech headaches—just a smooth, safe move.</li>
      </ul>

