      <h3 style="margin:0 0 10px">What is a Plex Server and Why You Might Want One</h3>
      <p><b>Think of Plex as your own personal Netflix.</b><br>
      Instead of paying for streaming subscriptions to access movies and shows you already own, Plex turns your PC or Mac into a media server.
      This means all your movies, TV shows, music, and even home videos live in one place — and you can enjoy them on any device in your home, like a smart TV, phone, or tablet.</p>

      <h4 style="margin:14px 0 6px">Why You Need It</h4>
      <ul style="margin:0 0 10px 20px">
        <li><b>One Library for Everything:</b> Plex organizes your collection with cover art, titles, and categories, making it easy to browse just like Netflix.</li>
        <li><b>Simple Backups:</b> We’ll place easy-to-use icons on your Zorin desktop so you can back up your media to a Plex folder with a single click.</li>
        <li><b>Expandable Storage:</b> If your drive isn’t big enough, we can upgrade it or use an external USB drive.</li>
        <li><b>Smart TV Ready:</b> Many smart TVs (like Samsung) already include the Plex app for quick, easy viewing.</li>
      </ul>

      <h4 style="margin:14px 0 6px">Local vs. Remote</h4>
      <p><b>Local Use (Included):</b> We configure Plex to work perfectly inside your home network — anyone on your Wi-Fi can watch from TVs, phones, tablets, or laptops.</p>
      <p><b>Remote Access (Optional):</b> Stream your library away from home. Requires router configuration and testing; offered as an advanced service at <b>$120/hr</b>.</p>

      <h4 style="margin:14px 0 6px">Licensing</h4>
      <p>To unlock all features, a Plex license (<b>Plex Pass</b>) is required. We can help you purchase and activate it so everything runs smoothly from day one.</p>

      <p style="margin:12px 0"><b>✅ Bottom Line:</b> With Plex, your Zorin computer becomes the heart of your entertainment system. We make sure your media is organized, backed up, and ready to enjoy — whether you’re watching on your computer, a smart TV, or mobile devices.</p>

